## ADR #01 — Secrets live only in `.env`, enforced by pre-commit (status: accepted)

**Context:** A repo read by AI agents and humans will accumulate credentials. Leaked
secrets in git history are expensive to purge and impossible to fully revoke.

**Decision:** All secrets live in `.env` (gitignored, `chmod 600` on prod) using the
`{{SERVICE_PREFIX}}_` prefix. A pre-commit hook (`scripts/pre-commit/check_secrets.sh`)
greps staged files for private keys / cloud credentials / committed `.env` and blocks
the commit. `.env.example` documents every variable with placeholder values.

**Consequences:** Hardcoding a secret, committing a real `.env`, or bypassing the hook
(`--no-verify`) without explicit human sign-off becomes an anti-pattern. A Vault /
Secrets-Manager migration, if ever needed, gets its own ADR.

